Author: DanielBMarkham
Content:
You don't think Frankl tackles head-on the meaning of existence? I mean, he's the father of logotherapy, which, as Wiki describes it, is "a type of Existential Analysis that focuses on a 'will to meaning' as opposed to Adler's Nietzschian doctrine of 'will to power' or Freud's of 'will to pleasure;'."

\nCan't get much more specific about dealing with existential crises than that, right?

Content: Interesting that in the beginning most article submissions were by the founders themselves. I don't use reddit, but I wonder if the frequent bemoaning of "when Reddit still was cool" I read here really refers to that time in the beginning when submissions were primarily made by the founders?
